FBIS4-34393 "drlat118_o_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 Colombia `Terrorists' Detonate Three Bombs, Damage Banks `Terrorists' Detonate Three Bombs, Damage Banks PA1806205294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal A Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 18 Jun 94 PA1806205294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal A Network Spanish BFN [From the "NTC News" newscast] [Text] A new wave of terror has been unleashed by terrorists who detonated three powerful bombs damaging three banks along the border. [not further specified] The shock wave caused damage estimated at more than 100 million pesos. The automatic tellers were destroyed, and a customer, who was seriously injured by the explosion, fights for his life. No specific subversive group has claimed responsibility for the attack.
